# Stakez – Gambling Awareness Simulator

A simulation web app inspired by Stake.com that educates users on how gambling platforms can manipulate outcomes. Includes a rig-toggle feature to demonstrate the difference between fair and biased play.

## 🌐 Live Demo
[Try Stakez](https://stakez.netlify.app/)


## 🎮 Features
- Inspired by popular gambling interfaces
- Toggle between **fair** and **rigged** outcomes
- Real-time display of game results and win/loss feedback
- Educational aim: exposes manipulation techniques in online gambling
- Lightweight, responsive, and fast

## 🛠️ Tech Stack
- HTML5
- CSS3
- JavaScript (Vanilla)

## 🧠 Learning Outcomes
- DOM manipulation and event-driven design
- Probability simulation in JavaScript
- UI/UX for educational simulations

## 📦 Installation (for local use)
1. Clone the repository  
   `git clone https://github.com/darshanbhatarkar/stakez.git`
2. Open `index.html` in your browser

## 📄 License
This project is for awareness and educational demonstration only. Not intended for real gambling use.
